# Engine editing rules

These rules apply when editing the framework engine: workflow rules, templates, workflow spec, agent definitions, slash commands, or skills.

When the workspace state is `distribution_mode: framework-template` and `instance_status: not_applied`, engine edits are framework maintenance. Do not require onboarding, service catalog, generated service coders, or service brain freshness unless the task also touches application source under `services/<service-name>/`.

## Scope

- `.agent/rules/`, `.agent/templates/`, `.agent/docs/`, `.agent/workflow.md` are **framework spec** — change cascades to every project using this framework.
- `.claude/agents/workflow/<name>.agent.md` (coordinator, onboarding, task-analysis, coder-leader, dev-verification, qc-handoff, qc-runner, bug-router, memory-update, workflow-policy, agent-factory, solution-architect) are **workflow agent definitions** — owned by framework.
- `.claude/agents/specialists/<category>/<name>.agent.md` are the **19 specialist advisors** (advisor-only, see R-016) — owned by framework. Categories: architecture, quality-security, product, data-ai, ops-devex, research-qa.
- `.claude/agents/coders/coder-infra.agent.md` and `coder-database.agent.md` are **built-in cross-cutting coders** — owned by framework.
- `.claude/agents/coders/coder-<service>.agent.md` are **generated coders** — created by `agent-factory` after user approval.
- `scripts/hooks/*` + `.claude/settings.json` PreToolUse are the **Claude enforcement hooks** (parity with `.cursor/hooks/*`, see R-017) — owned by framework.

## Editing policy

- Workflow rule changes require explicit user approval (R-011-08) and a CHANGELOG entry.
- Trivial framework maintenance may use workflow.md §6.2 lightweight fast-track evidence instead of full task artifacts when it does not affect approval gates, security rules, state machine, generated coder scopes, destructive behavior, or application code.
- Template additions/changes must keep backward compatibility (or bump a major version + migration note).
- Slash command changes must preserve the contract documented in `COMMAND.md`.
- Skill changes route through `/skills` command; do not mutate `skills-lock.json` or installed `SKILL.md` directly from implementation tasks (R-014-15).

## Cross-tool consistency

When changing engine files, also update:
- `AGENTS.md` (root, tool-agnostic) — if user-facing contract changed.
- `.codex/AGENTS.md`, `.cursor/rules/`, `.gemini/GEMINI.md`, `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — if tool-specific path references changed.
- `.agent/changelog.md` and `CHANGELOG.md`.

## Never

- Do not delete workflow agents from `.claude/agents/workflow/` or specialist advisors from `.claude/agents/specialists/`.
- Do not move framework engine paths without updating all references (the moves are tracked in CHANGELOG).
- Do not bypass approval gates by editing rules to remove the check (R-011-08).
